items.text:
CASTING CALL (ul√∏nnet)

Til et kortfilmsprojekt med arbejdstitlen ‚ÄúVISIT‚Äù s√∏ger vi 3 skuespillere til b√¶rende roller

üó∫Ô∏è AARHUS

üóìÔ∏è 5. - 10. FEBRUAR (+ bufferdag 11. februar)

FRIDA (Hovedrolle)

Spillealder: 22-28

MARCEL (Hovedrolle)

Spillealder: 20-28

DEN FREMMEDE (B√¶rende bi-rolle)

Spillealder: 24-30

OM FILMEN:

Frida og Marcel er begge midt i tyverne og er begge p√• hver sin m√•de g√•et i st√• i tilv√¶relsen. Frida f√∏ler, at hun sidder fast i sit ellers billedsk√∏nne og perfekte parforhold, og Marcel er lige blevet dumpet af pigen, han troede var sit livs k√¶rlighed.

I to parallelle handlingsforl√∏b kaster de sig ud i to vidt forskellige fors√∏g p√• at genfinde gnisten i den gr√• tilv√¶relse, p√• to forskellige dates, i to forskellige lejligheder p√• hver sin side af en opgang.

Vi er st√∏ttet af Aarhus Filmv√¶rksted, men er stadig en lavbudget-produktion drevet af passionerede frivillige. Projektet er derfor ikke l√∏nnet, men produktionen d√¶kker transport, samt m√•ltider og forfriskninger p√• set.

üìß Send en mail til [visitkortfilm@gmail.com](mailto:visitkortfilm@gmail.com) med titlen ‚ÄúCasting‚Äù efterfulgt af dit navn.

Vedh√¶ft et vellignende billede og eventuelt showreel/CV eller lignende - s√• kontakter vi dig med mere information.

May be a doodle of text that says 'FRIDA Perfekt liv, Perfekt forhold. Fastl√§st. Succesfuld, ung kvinde. Hun lever i et glansbillede af parforholdslykke og karrieremessig succes. Under facaden er hun rastlos. Playing age: 22-28 Enhver etnicitet On set dage: 5.-8. februar (Mulige pickups d. 11.)'

May be a graphic of text that says 'MARCEL En ung mand. Flot. Privilegeret. Hablos. Marcel forsoger at etablere et nyt liv, men kan knap overskue at skulle indrette sin nye lejlighed. Folsom og loyal, men ogsa passivt famlende, fanget nostalgi. Playing age: 20-28 Enhver etnicitet On set dage: 8.-10. februar (Mulige pickups d. 11.)'

Han pendler mellem sort humor, pseudo-dybsindige bemeerkninger og reelle risikohandlinger. Playing age: 24-30 Enhver etnicitet On set dage: 5.-7. februar (Mulige pickups 11.)'

message.text:
He still thinks this is his era.
Forty years old.
Hanging around like someone‚Äôs about to tap him on the shoulder and say ‚Äúyour time‚Äôs come.‚Äù

This is Callum.
Low level grunt.
Full time hanger-on.
Part time hard man.

In No Gentle Goodnight, Callum isn‚Äôt feared.
He‚Äôs tolerated.
Useful when someone needs a door standing near.
Disposable when they don‚Äôt.

He knows it too.
That‚Äôs why he stays.

Get a job.
Or get in the sea.

üé¨ Micro-trailer dropping
Try not to laugh.

message.text:
Mark Jenkinson.
A clenched fist in a town begging for a punch.

He holds it in.
Runs the gym.
Keeps the kids off the streets.

He‚Äôs been ready to explode for years.

He could level the place.
But staying quiet keeps them safe.

Then David comes back.
And David lights the fuse.

When Mark finally swings,
the impact hits twice as hard.

#NoGentleGoodnight #MarkJenkinson #ReadyToExplode #PressureCooker #SmallTownRot #BritishIndie #GrittyDrama

items.text:
Hello,

My name is Allison and I am the producer for the Student Short Film** ‚ÄúSoundly Awake‚Äù** at VFS Film Production Program. We are currently looking for Non-Union Actors to cast in our film!

**Project Title:** Soundly Awake

**Project Type:** Student Short Film

**Union Status: **Non-Union

**Director:** Raj Heer

**Producer:** Allison Wall

**Casting Director:** Allison Wall

**Audition Dates:** Self-tapes due by January 8th, 2026

**Audition Location:** Self-tapes only

**Call Back Dates:** January 11th, 2026

**Call Back Location:** 142 Water Street, Vancouver, BC V6B 1B2

**Shooting Dates: **January 27th - January 29th  

**Shooting Location:** Greater Vancouver Area

**Rates:** Unpaid. Catering and craft service provided.

**Submission Instructions:**

Please submit resume, headshot, and demo reel (if applicable) to soundlyawakefilm@gmail.com and indicate which role you‚Äôd like to be considered for.

**Synopsis:**

Haunted by recurring nightmares of his abusive father, Jun, a lonely and withdrawn man, meets Sage, a curious nightmare eater who appears to ‚Äúconsume‚Äù his pain. As Sage helps ease Jun‚Äôs suffering in the Between, Jun begins to open his heart, finding the strength to confront his father in the real world. When the nightmares end and Sage has to leave, Jun is heartbroken, fearing he will never see Sage again, until an unexpected reunion proves that some bonds endure beyond dreams.

Die Musikwirtschaft schafft in √ñsterreich j√§hrlich rund 7,5 Milliarden Euro an Wertsch√∂pfung ‚Äì das sind etwa 2,8 % des gesamten BIP. √úber 117.000 Arbeitspl√§tze h√§ngen direkt oder indirekt an ihr, also mehr als in der IT- oder Finanzbranche. Dazu kommen rund 4,3 Milliarden Euro an Steuereffekten. Damit wird deutlich, wie stark die Branche wirtschaftlich wirkt ‚Äì und das nicht nur im eigenen Bereich: Musik setzt wichtige Impulse f√ºr Tourismus, Kultur und die gesamte Kreativszene.
Die zugrunde liegende Studie (2024) stammt von Paul und Collegen Consulting, beauftragt von FAMA, ifpi sowie AKM/austromechana.

12/12/25

(This Is My) Family (Short Film)

A Comedy about family dynamics

A family near breaking point, implodes in one night. 

Shooting April location TBC

Auditioning: We want to receive self tapes first and those who make it to the next stage, we would love in person auditions by late January of 2026. 

Travel Expenses paid

Student film being screened at The BFI and will be entered into film festivals

Elizabeth (50s-60s) - Narcissistic mother who dominates her kids' lives. She speaks her mind much to the reluctance of everyone around her..

Marie (30s-40s) - She‚Äôs in the middle of a mid-life crisis and she blames elizabeth as she thinks she‚Äôs not the perfect mother that she presents herself as. So Marie rebels against this supposed ‚Äòperfect family‚Äô.

Shaun (30-40s) - Shaun simply accepts his place in the world and has very little self respect. He is in a loveless relationship with his wife (Claire) however he does not rebel against her out of fear of living life alone in his 40s. Yet again every man has his breaking point. 

Clare (30s-40s) - Clare needs power and control, so she has found a man she can excerpt this power on (Shaun.) Clare and Elizabeth are very similar and therefore team up to inflate each other's egos at the expense of Marie and Shaun. 

Email: tylerbrownework@gmail.com for further details

Please only respond if you are based in England as our budget will not cover travel from abroad.

items.text:
We are casting confident, expressive individuals to appear as contestants/guests on a high-energy, unscripted talk show inspired by classic formats such as Jeremy Kyle and Jerry Springer.

The show will be hosted by massive influencer, who will take the role of the presenter, guiding conversations, mediating disputes, and attempting to resolve real or semi-scripted personal conflicts in an entertaining, fast-paced environment.

This is a performance-based role requiring strong personality, emotional range, and the ability to react naturally on camera.

Role Description ‚Äì Contestants / Guests

Selected participants will appear on the show as individuals involved in a personal conflict, relationship issue, family dispute, secret reveal, or moral dilemma. Scenarios may include (but are not limited to):

Relationship breakdowns or accusations

Love triangles or cheating allegations

Friendship or family fallouts

Hidden secrets or confrontations

Lifestyle or behavioural conflicts

You will be expected to:

Play a character or heightened version of yourself

Engage in open, confrontational, or emotionally charged discussions

React naturally to questions, accusations, and audience/chat interaction

Remain in character throughout the segment

Be comfortable with raised voices, dramatic moments, and comedic tension

Ideal Candidate

Aged 18+

Confident and expressive on camera

Comfortable with confrontation and emotional performance

Strong improvisation skills (acting experience is a plus, but not required)

Able to think quickly and respond naturally in live situations

Thick-skinned and comfortable being part of viral, high-reach content

Important Notes

This is entertainment content, not a real counselling or therapy show

Scenarios may be planned, semi-scripted, or improvised

Content will be broadcast live and clipped for social platforms (TikTok, Instagram, YouTube, etc.)

Applicants must consent to being filmed and distributed online

Compensation

Paid role

Rate dependent on role complexity, screen time, and experience

topComments.text: Looking for uneducated thickos with anger problems. Got it.
People who wash their dirty linen in public for cash .  Have we not grown out of these shows .

items.previewDescription: Since 2007 Eagles Nest Theatre has performed in Victoria, across Australia and overseas. We run one of the biggest Theatre Education programs in Victoria.

sharedPost.text:
WOMEN ACTORS - Min 30 plus - pref 35-40 plus

Eagle‚Äôs Nest Theatre in Melbourne Australia is looking for 1 or 2 new leading for Women for 2026 

Parts up for grabs are Lady Macbeth and Jocasta (Oedipus)

More info about the company here

https://eaglesnesttheatre.com/ 

‚Äî

About the gig 

Great chance to have ongoing quality creative work but a small enough number of gigs that have time for other work / life commitments. 

Its our school's program -  ea h gig is 2h (1h condensed performance, 1h workshop revisiting key scenes)

Current Gig Dates

OEDIPUS
Jan 30
Feb 12, 26
April 2
May 6, 20, 29
June 17 (two performances)
July 22, 30
Aug 5 

MACBETH
Feb 20 (two performances)
May 4, 6
Aug 3
Sept 7, 10
Oct 16

NB - Some flexibility to be able to take addition gig dates and accomdate date changes is important.  

This is Co-Op gig. It pays a per Gig Fee but not at award rates. Rehearsals are unpaid.

The gig could be right for you if you like earning a few bucks doing great creative work, not if you are needing a job to pay the mortgage. Lol 

‚Äî--

Applications. 

We are not doing formal auditions at applications at this stage. 

I have time over the next two weeks to speak to a few individual actors and possibly get a few in for a read.

Who knows maybe we hit the Jackpot pre Xmas and dont have to audition in Jan.  

If you have the availability for the dates above, interest for next year and skills to deliver some big shows send me a message.

Direct facebook message or

Whatsapp Text +61423339431 

WHAT I NEED IN YOUR MESSAGE

1-2 sentence max about your acting/live performance/stage experience. (Please dont submit CV‚Äôs - prior Shakespeare or Greek drama exp valuable but not required)

1-2 sentences max about why this is a good creative fit for u 

A picture of you (pref head to toe) 

Age and hight. 

‚Äî-

Messages only - Please do not call. 

Phone chats will be organised after checking dates and $ to make sure we are not wasting each other's time. 

Meetings / auditions allocated on the basis of phone discussions

‚Äî-

Other castings 

Ps - we will soon be doing a call out for men under 25 and men over 30 preferable over 35.

If you or someone you know fits the casting requirements in this post please get in touch asap. 

Would prefer to allocate time to people who come recommended 

Cheers

James

items.text: New to this group and would love to follow my dream of becoming an actor, what are my chances, im 41 years old of an athletic build, English and fluent in Spanish, have experience in mixed martial arts, south east accent but can also do a multitude of accents too, any tips advice would be much appreciated.

topComments.text: Join a local Amateur Dramatics society to find out if you CAN act, as it is a talent that not everyone possesses.  Then, if you‚Äôre any good, get some professional training, a show reel, good headshots and apply to lots of agents for representation.

I started my acting journey at 50. After some extra work, i realised wanted speaking parts, so I i auditioned for a screen acting course - as I wanted feedback/coaching. I then got professional headshos and started with setting up a profile on Mandy, for me unpaid student films were a great training ground and I also got paid work for social media adverts. From there i expanded onto Backstage, Star Now and Talent Talks. The paid work I got booked for enabled me to get onto Spotlight and get an agent. All little steps towards my dream. Lots of learning on the way, such as how to self tape. Good luck

CASTING CALL ‚Äì BATH

We‚Äôre looking for two actors for a 1600s period-drama music video filming in Bath. 
This is an unpaid collaborative project and we‚Äôre aiming for atmospheric, experimental, vintage-horror-style performances.

‚∏ª

FEMALE ACTOR (18‚Äì30) ‚Äì ‚ÄúAgnes‚Äù

A farmer‚Äôs daughter with a wide emotional range, from love to rage.
‚Ä¢ Experimental physical performance (no audio recorded)
‚Ä¢ Period-accurate clothing, minimal/no makeup
‚Ä¢ White/European descent
‚Ä¢ Please send: headshot, showreel, cover letter

‚∏ª

MALE ACTOR (18‚Äì35)

A wealthy, confident, and devious character who tries to charm Agnes. Includes a scene where he becomes possessed and shifts into a zombie-like state.
‚Ä¢ Strong physical storytelling (no audio recorded)
‚Ä¢ Period-accurate clothing, minimal/no makeup
‚Ä¢ Please send: headshot, showreel, cover letter

‚∏ª

If you fit either brief and are interested, please email coleoakley101@gmail.com to apply with the required materials.

Thank you.

items.text:
Free Showreel Offer

Full booked for now. But I'll definitely be doing this again so if you're interested follow Lizzie.LuluProductions   for more opportunities. Thanks everyone! x

Hi everyone!

I've been volunteering in the filmmaking world for about a year now, and I still have a lot to learn. I'm currently offering free showreels to actors based in Yorkshire as a way to build up my camera operating and directing portfolio.

I‚Äôve written lots of new scripts, and I'm planning another showreel day on either the 28th, the 30th of December, or the 2nd of January.

Each showreel will take around 45 minutes to film. I'm happy to pair people up, but if you'd prefer to arrange your own scene partner, that‚Äôs absolutely fine too!

If you're interested, please message me or email lizzieluluproductions@gmail.com ‚Äî I‚Äôd love to hear from you! Please only email if you are interested as I have lots of people emailing but then ignoring me when they receive their call times.

Many thanks. x

Die Musikwirtschaft schafft in √ñsterreich j√§hrlich rund 7,5 Milliarden Euro an Wertsch√∂pfung ‚Äì das sind etwa 2,8 % des gesamten BIP. √úber 117.000 Arbeitspl√§tze h√§ngen direkt oder indirekt an ihr, also mehr als in der IT- oder Finanzbranche. Dazu kommen rund 4,3 Milliarden Euro an Steuereffekten. Damit wird deutlich, wie stark die Branche wirtschaftlich wirkt ‚Äì und das nicht nur im eigenen Bereich: Musik setzt wichtige Impulse f√ºr Tourismus, Kultur und die gesamte Kreativszene.

CASTING CALL for Manchester-based student comedy short film '(GONE WRONG)'

The film follows two aspiring content creators trying to record a Chris Hansen-style video confronting what they believe to be a child predator. However, things go horribly wrong when the predator they've lured out turns out to not be a man pretending to be a child, but instead an actual child!!!

If interested, please Contact me directly via Instagram or Facebook, or email me at Hmorton1@futureworks.ac.uk

items.text:
Unpaid actor 

Hello. I am Grace, I am an ametur filmmaking, I am currently working on a mix media horror project called The Haven Institute. I am looking for a male actor to play the role of Young Nigel Harrow (AGE 20-23, set in 90s). This is currently as a backup so I have a range of actors to chose. What is required is that I will send over a block of script lasting around 3 minutes each (currently there are 7) and I will need the actor to film these clips in their time and their own environment. Location doesn't matter. This project is unpaid.

If you are interested or have any more questions please drop me an email at Thehollowreturn@outlook.com 

Diolch

items.text:
I recently had a detailed conversation with Kurt Evans of Artist2Artist, one of the established actor showcase platforms, specifically around demo reels, self-tapes, and how casting actually encounters actors.

A few points from that discussion are worth sharing, because they clarify a lot of confusion I keep seeing among actors at different stages.

On demo reels:
Casting directors are not ignoring traditional demo reels. A professional demo reel is still exactly that ‚Äî the professional work you‚Äôve done, compiled into a roughly three-minute video. What matters is how that reel is structured.

Rather than one or two long scenes, the reel works best when it‚Äôs made up of multiple 20‚Äì30 second sections, each clearly showing a type you would naturally be called in for ‚Äî parent, authority figure, professional roles, etc. The goal isn‚Äôt to replace the reel, but to make it immediately readable. Realistically, a director may only watch about 20 seconds before deciding whether you fit, so clarity matters more than length.

On highly produced self-tapes:
We spoke about the rise of very cinematic, highly produced self-tapes ‚Äî essentially mini-movies. Kurt isn‚Äôt against production value. In fact, he shared an example where one panelist loved a highly edited tape, while another felt it looked more like a finished production than an audition.

The key point he emphasized is that the purpose of a self-tape or showcase submission is still to evaluate acting. Most actors audition two to three times a week. It‚Äôs neither realistic nor necessary to shoot a short film every time. What casting needs is a clear window into the performance. Overproduction isn‚Äôt a mistake ‚Äî it‚Äôs just not what casting is primarily judging.

On agents and casting access:
This is the part many actors misunderstand. Casting primarily encounters actors through agents. It‚Äôs not about gatekeeping or access ‚Äî it‚Äôs how the system functions. There‚Äôs a trust relationship between agents and casting offices.

In a traditional setting, a casting assistant may block off hours of time, receive hundreds of short submissions from agents, and narrow those down to about twenty strong fits. That‚Äôs how casting begins to connect with talent. Without representation, casting offices often have no way of knowing an actor exists.

What showcases like Artist2Artist aim to do is create a space where casting can watch actors work outside the volume and time pressure of the standard submission pipeline.

The takeaway from the conversation was straightforward:
For actors who want to be seen consistently in film and television, representation is the first gateway into that ecosystem.

items.text:
I recently had a detailed conversation with Kurt Evans of Artist2Artist, one of the established actor showcase platforms, specifically around demo reels, self-tapes, and how casting actually encounters actors.

A few points from that discussion are worth sharing, because they clarify a lot of confusion I keep seeing among actors at different stages.

On demo reels:
Casting directors are not ignoring traditional demo reels. A professional demo reel is still exactly that ‚Äî the professional work you‚Äôve done, compiled into a roughly three-minute video. What matters is how that reel is structured.

Rather than one or two long scenes, the reel works best when it‚Äôs made up of multiple 20‚Äì30 second sections, each clearly showing a type you would naturally be called in for ‚Äî parent, authority figure, professional roles, etc. The goal isn‚Äôt to replace the reel, but to make it immediately readable. Realistically, a director may only watch about 20 seconds before deciding whether you fit, so clarity matters more than length.

On highly produced self-tapes:
We spoke about the rise of very cinematic, highly produced self-tapes ‚Äî essentially mini-movies. Kurt isn‚Äôt against production value. In fact, he shared an example where one panelist loved a highly edited tape, while another felt it looked more like a finished production than an audition.

The key point he emphasized is that the purpose of a self-tape or showcase submission is still to evaluate acting. Most actors audition two to three times a week. It‚Äôs neither realistic nor necessary to shoot a short film every time. What casting needs is a clear window into the performance. Overproduction isn‚Äôt a mistake ‚Äî it‚Äôs just not what casting is primarily judging.

On agents and casting access:
This is the part many actors misunderstand. Casting primarily encounters actors through agents. It‚Äôs not about gatekeeping or access ‚Äî it‚Äôs how the system functions. There‚Äôs a trust relationship between agents and casting offices.

In a traditional setting, a casting assistant may block off hours of time, receive hundreds of short submissions from agents, and narrow those down to about twenty strong fits. That‚Äôs how casting begins to connect with talent. Without representation, casting offices often have no way of knowing an actor exists.

What showcases like Artist2Artist aim to do is create a space where casting can watch actors work outside the volume and time pressure of the standard submission pipeline.

The takeaway from the conversation was straightforward:
For actors who want to be seen consistently in film and television, representation is the first gateway into that ecosystem.

FREE HEADSHOT with any of my packages - my Christmas gift to you.

Book a session by Christmas (the shoot itself can take place before or in the New Year) and I‚Äôll include one extra headshot completely free.

My studio is fully portable, so I can travel to you if you‚Äôd prefer the ease of shooting at home, or you‚Äôre welcome to come to my studio in Grantham, Lincolnshire.

or feel free to message me directly here on FB.

items.text:
‚≠ê OFFICIAL CASTING CALL 

Building a Core Acting Team for a New Film/Stage Universe

I‚Äôm assembling a core long-term team (like Kevin Hart‚Äôs Plastic Cup Boyz / Adam Sandler‚Äôs crew) to develop a new film universe plus multiple original projects.

Phase 1:
A small stage adaptation of my book (just to get everyone in sync).

Phase 2:
We turn that story into our first feature film.

Phase 3 and beyond:
Continuous films inside the Frenchie Extended Universe + original projects outside the universe.
Everyone on the core team will be acting, producing, writing, and helping shape future projects together.

Roles Currently Casting (Core Team Only):

Riley (F) ‚Äì Love interest of the main character. Loyal, grounded, warm energy.

Isabella (F, Puerto Rican) ‚Äì Fierce, supportive, emotional backbone of the group.

Crumbs (M) ‚Äì Comedic timing, lovable troublemaker.

Jordan (M) ‚Äì Serious, loyal, big heart but stern presence.

Marcus (M, Black) ‚Äì Later-series antagonist; charismatic, powerful, intimidating.

Jimmy/Frenchie (M) ‚Äì Already cast.

What I need from you:

Send me a 30‚Äì45 second video reading a short line for the character you‚Äôre interested in.
Nothing fancy ‚Äî I just need to see presence, expression, and vibe.

What this is NOT:

This is NOT a one-off gig or a ‚Äúshow up, get paid, leave‚Äù job.
This is a long-term creative family building something from scratch together.

What this IS:

‚úî A team
‚úî A pipeline
‚úî A chance to grow into acting/producing/directing
‚úî Multiple projects ahead
‚úî Long-term involvement as the universe expands

If you‚Äôre hungry, reliable, and want to build something real ‚Äî comment INTERESTED and I‚Äôll DM you a line to read.

Let‚Äôs build something Buffalo can be proud of. üî•
‚Äî Jimmy

Hello!

Currently at the start of the casting process for the workshop version of my show next September!

(including 2 presentation milestones in February and June - more production details upon invite)

If you are a queer identifying musical theatre performer and feel aligned with the piece I would love to have you!

PS. Please note this is a university funded production and due to guidelines I am not allowed to pay anyone for their time. Please keep this in mind if you are thinking of applying and know that your time and energy will be deeply appreciated in other ways. Hoping for this to be only the beginning!

Loooove,

Chris xx

10,000 followers.

Honestly‚Ä¶ thank you.

The support, the shares, the messages, the belief, it means more than we can put into words.

Every follow, every comment, every bit of encouragement has helped shape what this is becoming. We don‚Äôt take a single one of you for granted.

From the bottom of our hearts, thank you for being part of the journey.

items.text:
Hi! We are LOOKING FOR A MALE ACTOR for a short film here in Budapest, set during World War II, and we aim to shoot over 2 days in late February 2026 in the H≈±v√∂sv√∂lgy area.

The title for the film is KITART√ÅS. It is a short film set during the Siege of Budapest and is a psychological exploration of the raw emotional cost in war times. The story follows Hungarian soldiers as they face a moral and physical struggle for survival in the last year of the war in Hungary. The role requires fluency in both English (for crew communication/rehearsals) and Hungarian (as the film's dialogue will be in Hungarian).

The short film will be submitted to local and international film festivalsüé¨

This is a low-budget short film, but it will have a symbolic paymentüí∞

We are looking for a person to play one of the lead roles.

√ÅD√ÅM:

Character Description: A Hungarian soldier under Istv√°n‚Äôs command. √Åd√°m is a man torn between obedience to his orders and the stirrings of his own conscience and guilt. His internal conflict becomes a major turning point in the film.

Requirements:

Male, 25‚Äì30 years old.

1.75cm - 1.80cm 

Fit or in a healthy weight

Strong presence

Must speak English and Hungarian fluently

Comfortable performing in outdoor winter conditions.

Strong dramatic ability and emotional range.

If you would like to be considered, please send your headshots, short introduction, and (if available) a showreel or acting CV to:

‚úâÔ∏è contactingdianag@gmail.com

Deadline: 31/12/2025

üö® STOP SCROLLING üö®
Right. We‚Äôve tried to keep this quiet. We‚Äôve failed. The cat is out of the bag and it‚Äôs doing laps of Sunny Runny HQ.

Something BIG has been bubbling away behind the scenes and it‚Äôs finally time to say it out loud‚Ä¶

üé∫ü•Å FANFARE PLEASE ü•Åüé∫

WELCOME TO THE SUNNY RUNNY COMEDY PODCAST AND SKETCH SHOW üéôÔ∏è

From January we‚Äôre launching a weekly podcast where we‚Äôll be talking hot topics, life, nonsense and whatever else spirals out of control. We‚Äôll be unleashing characters we‚Äôve been secretly writing for months, plus a completely new interview format that absolutely should not work but somehow does.

This is not your usual sit-around-and-chat podcast. We‚Äôre binning the formula and doing something brand new, unhinged, novel and slightly dangerous. Side-splitting. Questionable. Probably a bad idea. Exactly our kind of thing.

Tell yer mates. Tell yer ma. Tell that one group chat that never shuts up.
Big things are coming to Sunny Runny.

And a massive welcome to Mike from Reel Productions, The Studio. who‚Äôs brave enough to collaborate with us on this chaos.

#SunnyRunny #ComedyPodcast #SketchComedy #UKComedy #NewPodcast #PodcastLaunch #ChaoticGood #ContentCreators #ReelProductions

items.text:
Hey!

Wir produzieren f√ºr die lokalen For-Future-Gruppen der Region T√ºbingen satirische Beitr√§ge, die an "Die Anstalt" (ZDF) angelehnt sind und haben deswegen noch einige Rollen zu besetzen.

Kurzum versucht Mutter Natur in einem fiktiven Gerichtsraum gegen Friedrich Merz das Recht zu erstreiten, endlich als juristische Person wahrgenommen zu werden. Dabei helfen ihr Zeugen wie "Die Psyche der Menschen", "Der Vorgarten" und "Der Begradigte Fluss". Da das Format nicht nur satirisch-humoristisch ist, sondern auch einen informativen Charakter hat, wird das Projekt sehr dialoglastig sein. 

üìçWir drehen in T√ºbingen. 

üïû Geplant sind 1-2 Drehtage im Zeitraum Anfang bis Ende Februar 2026 (genauere Informationen folgen)

üé¨ Logline: In ihrem Ziel, das erste Mal als juristisches Subjekt wahrgenommen zu werden kommt es zu einer Konfrontation mit Friedrich Merz. 

üíµ Wir sind eine No-Budget-Produktion, weshalb wir leider keine keine Gagen vergeben k√∂nnen.

Anbei ist unsere Projektmappe und Moodboard, die Rollen sind dort noch mal ausf√ºhrlich beschrieben. 

Schreibt uns bei Interesse eine E-mail, in der ihr euch kurz vorstellt - wir melden uns dann zur√ºck!

im.namen.der.natur@gmail.com

Wir freuen uns!

Liebe Gr√º√üe,
Devid

**Casting Certified Fitness, Yoga & Pilates Trainers**
**PAID OPPORTUNITY**

Hello everyone!
I‚Äôm currently looking for **certified trainers** for an upcoming project with **a major activewear brand**. We are preparing a new series of social-media training videos and are now conducting a **preliminary casting**.

We‚Äôre looking for:
‚Ä¢ Fitness / functional training coaches
‚Ä¢ Yoga instructors
‚Ä¢ Pilates instructors
‚Ä¢ Stretching / mobility specialists

We welcome trainers of **different ages and backgrounds**, as long as you are certified, experienced, and confident working with beginner-level clients.

The project includes participation in **on-camera training shoots**.
Details regarding filming dates and compensation will be discussed individually with selected candidates.

If you:
‚Ä¢ hold valid certifications
‚Ä¢ have at least 5 years of teaching experience
‚Ä¢ have on-camera experience (a plus, but not required)
‚Ä¢ are open to collaboration

‚Äî please feel free to **DM me directly**.
When reaching out, include your training specialty and a link to your social media or examples of your teaching.

Looking forward to connecting with talented professionals!

CASTING/CREW CALL ‚Äì NEW DOCUMENTARY (Los Angeles, Jan/Feb 2026) 
ÔøΩFrom a TV Producer with Discovery & History Channel credits. 

I‚Äôm currently casting for a new documentary that explores the powerful stories we attach to the objects we treasure most. I‚Äôm looking for people who have one meaningful item something that, when held, brings back emotion, memory, or a story that shaped who you are.

Your object could be:
* A family heirloom
* A gift from someone who has passed
* A reminder of a relationship or life-changing moment
* Or simply something that holds deep, personal significance

This project will highlight everyday people and the extraordinary stories behind the things they hold dear.

FILMING:ÔøΩLos Angeles ‚Äî January & February 2026
If you have an item that carries emotional weight and a story you're willing to share on camera, I‚Äôd love to hear from you.

TO APPLY:ÔøΩPlease get in touch and share a brief description of yourself, your item, and the story behind it. Photos welcome but not required.
Looking forward to hearing your story.

EMAIL: breynolsbri@gmail.com
INSTAGRAM: @bryannareynolds

items.text:
In case you missed it‚Ä¶.

A special shout-out to Red Leg Brewing Company for being an absolutely amazing venue!

Get Ready, Denver!

The momentum continues! We are thrilled to announce we're heading to the Mile High City. We will be revealing the location and details for our Denver Networking Event happening in January very soon!

Follow us so you don't miss the announcement!

www.kickassfilmfest.com

sharedPost.text:
What an incredible night! A massive thank you to every filmmaker and creative who attended our Colorado Springs Meet-N-Greet on December 6th. The energy was electric, and the connections forged were exactly what these events are for: uniting newbies, veterans, and everyone in between for networking and potential new collaborators!

A special shout-out to Red Leg Brewing Company for being an absolutely amazing venue!

Get Ready, Denver!

The momentum continues! We are thrilled to announce we're heading to the Mile High City. We will be revealing the location and details for our Denver Networking Event happening in January very soon!

Follow us so you don't miss the announcement!

www.kickassfilmfest.com

#filmmaking #Networking #coloradosprings #denver #creativecommunity #kickassfilmfest #coloradofilm #filmproduction #filmmakerslife #filmcrew #Filmmakers

items.text:
Hello!

Currently at the start of the casting process for the workshop version of my show next September!

(including 2 presentation milestones in February and June - more production details upon invite)

If you are a queer identifying musical theatre performer and feel aligned with the piece I would love to have you!

PS. Please note this is a university funded production and due to guidelines I am not allowed to pay anyone for their time. Please keep this in mind if you are thinking of applying and know that your time and energy will be deeply appreciated in other ways. Hoping for this to be only the beginning!

Loooove,

Chris xx
